{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.13",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 13,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 13",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 13 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:1",
      "text": "Behold, mine eye has seen these things, and mine ear has heard them.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:2",
      "text": "And I know all that ye too know; and I have not less understanding than you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:3",
      "text": "Nevertheless I will speak to the Lord, and I will reason before him, if he will.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:4",
      "text": "But ye are all bad physicians, and healers of diseases.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:5",
      "text": "But would that ye were silent, and it would be wisdom to you in the end.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:6",
      "text": "But hear ye the reasoning of my mouth, and attend to the judgment of my lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:7",
      "text": "Do ye not speak before the Lord, and utter deceit before him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:8",
      "text": "Or will ye draw back? nay, do ye yourselves be judges.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:9",
      "text": "For it were well if he would thoroughly search you: for though doing all things in your power ye should attach yourselves to him,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:10",
      "text": "he will not reprove you at all the less: but if moreover ye should secretly respect persons,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:11",
      "text": "shall not his whirlpool sweep you round, and terror from him fall upon you?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:12",
      "text": "And your glorying shall prove in the end to you like ashes, and your body like a body of clay.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:13",
      "text": "Be silent, that I may speak, and cease from mine anger,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:14",
      "text": "while I may take my flesh in my teeth, and put my life in my hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:15",
      "text": "Though the Mighty One should lay hand upon me, forasmuch as he has begun, verily I will speak, and plead before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:16",
      "text": "And this shall turn to me for salvation; for fraud shall have no entrance before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:17",
      "text": "Hear, hear ye my words, for I will declare in your hearing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:18",
      "text": "Behold, I am near my judgment: I know that I shall appear evidently just.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:19",
      "text": "For who is he that shall plead with me, that I should now be silent, and expire?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:20",
      "text": "But grant me two things: then I will not hide myself from thy face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:21",
      "text": "Withhold thine hand from me: and let not thy fear terrify me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:22",
      "text": "Then shalt thou call, and I will hearken to thee: or thou shalt speak, and I will give thee an answer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:23",
      "text": "How many are my sins and my transgressions? teach me what they are.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:24",
      "text": "Wherefore hidest thou thyself from me, and deemest me thine enemy?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:25",
      "text": "Wilt thou be startled at me, as at a leaf shaken by the wind? or wilt thou set thyself against me as against grass borne upon the breeze?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:26",
      "text": "For thou hast written evil things against me, and thou hast compassed me with the sins of my youth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:27",
      "text": "And thou hast placed my foot in the stocks; and thou hast watched all my works, and hast penetrated to my heels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.13.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:28",
      "text": "I am as that which waxes old like a bottle, or like a moth-eaten garment.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
